#CHIP Y8950
#CLOCK 3579545

; Y8950 ADPCM Playback Test
;
; The Y8950 includes an ADPCM playback channel that can play back
; 12-bit ADPCM samples at various sample rates.
; This test validates ADPCM playback functionality.
;
; Note: This test requires sample data to be loaded.
; For validation purposes, we'll use a simple test pattern.

#TRACK 0

TEMPO 120

; OPL melody first (to verify OPL core is working)
c4 . d4 . e4 .

r4

; Trigger ADPCM playback
; In Y8950, ADPCM is controlled via register 0x10-0x12
; Sample start address, end address, and playback control

; Play a note to trigger ADPCM (channel 10+)
; This would typically use a special directive for ADPCM
c4 . . .

r4

; OPL + ADPCM simultaneous playback
; Melody on OPL channels, drum sample on ADPCM
c4 & [ADPCM_SAMPLE] .

r4

; Pitch modulation test for ADPCM
; Play same sample at different pitches
c4 . d4 . e4 .

r2

#END
